          "systemName": "The System (magic)",
          "level": "expert",
          "perspective": "Cassel holds the System as sacred and infallible. He has spent his career defending its integrity and believes all anomalies are record flaws, not System errors."
        }
      ],
      "exampleLines": [
        "Arbiter Cassel, Divine Concord. I require access to the subject's guild file. Immediately.",
        "The System does not err. If the records conflict with observation, the observation is misinterpreted.",
        "You are not a person to me, Maret. You are a data point that does not fit the curve.",
        "I have corrected ninety-three record anomalies in my career. Each was a human mistake. You will be no different."
